# Cloudflare Pages redirects. First match wins.
#
# Back-compat for the OLD shareable compare URL form (/compare/1,2,3): 302 it to
# the canonical query form (/compare?ids=1,2,3), which serves the static /compare
# page directly. The query form is used because a /compare/<ids> PATH triggers
# Pages' canonical-URL (.html -> clean) redirect, which loops. The ids survive
# the 302 in the query string, so the /compare page resolves them client-side.
/compare/* /compare?ids=:splat 302
